From 3a0691cfe4569ff53d610339d8a0b03e4f891d3d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mark Harfouche <mark@ramonaoptics.com>
Date: Sat, 16 May 2026 22:40:01 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 9/9] Annotate the remaining public C++ API with ONNX_API

Several public functions in checker.h, inliner.h, schema.h,
shape_inference/implementation.h and printer.h were not annotated with
ONNX_API, so they were not exported from the ONNX shared library on
Windows and a separate consumer (onnx_cpp2py_export) failed to link
against them. Annotate the checker free functions, the inliner entry
points, OpSchema::Verify, the shape-inference helpers and the proto
streaming operators.

Also drop ONNX_API from the RegisterOpSetSchema function template: a
template is instantiated in every translation unit, so a definition
carrying __declspec(dllimport) is rejected by MSVC (C2491).
---
 onnx/checker.h                        | 22 ++++++++++-----------
 onnx/defs/printer.h                   | 28 +++++++++++++--------------
 onnx/defs/schema.h                    |  6 ++++--
 onnx/inliner/inliner.h                | 10 +++++-----
 onnx/shape_inference/implementation.h |  4 ++--
 5 files changed, 36 insertions(+), 34 deletions(-)

